website_summaries.verdict: A large quantity of treats by a trusted name in pet food. Most cats love them, and owners love the budget-friendly price.
pros: A value priced canister filled with 20 ounces of seafood flavors felines love – crab, tuna, and shrimp
Crunchy, and the resealable container keeps them fresh
cons: A few cat owners reported that their cats preferred other types of treats over them, but most were happy with these

customer_reviews.title: kind of crummy*
customer_reviews.text: When this product was delivered I found that more than 1/3 of of the container consisted of small crumbs that my cat would not eat. *After posting this review with 3 stars, I was contacted by the manufacturer and was provided with a replacement. The combination of an otherwise excellent product with prompt and courteous customer service makes this a 5 star review.
customer_reviews.author: Robert F. Brooker

customer_reviews.title: My cat LOVES these!
customer_reviews.text: Oh my God! My cat will not leave me alone anymore! These things are super dooper treats to her! She will do anything to get her mouth on these. Even letting me clip her nail, give her baths and a whole list of other things she used to fear. i am so happy we gave these a try. Talked to her vet as well and she tells me they are just mostly protein so they are fine in moderation. So buyer beware. You might have a super happy cat on your hands if you buy these! Very happy with my purchase!
customer_reviews.author: Alicia MTop Contributor: Camping

customer_reviews.title: Cat is OBSESSED
customer_reviews.text: Keep these above the toilet for our cat after she goes to the bathroom. She is toilet trained thanks to these treats! She goes in the toilet and then comes and finds me and meows at the top of her kitty vocals, waiting for one or two of these treats.
customer_reviews.author: Wheres Me Coffee

customer_reviews.title: Cat Crack
customer_reviews.text: Well *I* don't love it, because *I* don't eat it. But my three kitties love this stuff!! Wanna train your cats to do tricks or behave? Use this. My cats turn their nose up at Temptations and won't eat it, but THIS stuff... it's Cat Crack. My kitties are addicted to these treats. They'd knock me down and confiscate the container if they could figure out how to open the screw top cap.,
customer_reviews.author: Samantha Ashe

customer_reviews.title: The pets love these!
customer_reviews.text: My cats love these treats, and since they are older (14 and 15) I use them to entice them to eat more or add a few calories. They will knock each other over just trying to get them. The dog loves them too, but they are quite small, since it's for cats, so feeding by hand is difficult in larger dogs. This beats buying them in the smaller packets since we go through them pretty quick.
customer_reviews.author: A. KoubaTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: Tasty treats for all types of kitties
customer_reviews.text: The cats at the clinic that I work at are completely addicted to these treats. I was worried about getting a different flavor than what they were used to but they love this flavor too. Even the meanest cat that likes to hit people when she doesn't get what she wants turns into the sweetest kitty when these treats are out. The shy kitty comes out of hiding to get her treats and the quiet kitty starts chirping when she hears the container shake.
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth BrothersTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: Very handy for multiple cats
customer_reviews.text: My cats' favorite treats are the Purina Friskies Party Mix, Beachside Crunch. These are about the only ones they really enjoy. I was delighted to find them in a plastic jar because a bag or two of them doesn't last long with four cats who love their treats. They come in a 20 ounce reusable jar that can be refilled from the bags of treats if you'd like to do it that way. It's a very handy and practical way to keep your cats provided with their favorite goodies. My four cats appreciate it!
customer_reviews.author: S. Warfield

customer_reviews.title: really love 💙 their treats
customer_reviews.text: 😻😻My fur faces ( I know Lucy called Snoopy that-much to his chagrin-but my kids, at the moment, happen to be of the feline persuasion), really love 💙 their treats!! They gang up on me to try to get them more often than their morning and bedtime specified times!! They seem to be really happy 😄 with these. Theyre not particularly into some other brands or flavors. Check out the different prices even on Amazon. Some are cheaper than others. Good deals! Nice having them delivered so I don't run out when I can't find them on sale at the store.
customer_reviews.author: Sue Rae

customer_reviews.title: Orderd On Prime Now.. Diffrent Package & smell rotten smell.
customer_reviews.text: Ordered 2nd time prime now different package and 100% different smell.. cats initially refused one theb started eating they got sick.. WTF? Thin I may have to seek council on this one.. Stopped feeding cats recovering but destroyed immune system 2 cats requiring meds. Right is store Left is amazon.. WTF? Amazon!!
customer_reviews.author: Steven L. Rhine

customer_reviews.title: Cats Rating
customer_reviews.text: This is how our cats rate this product since I can't really judge. All I can say is they really enjoy this brand and flavor as an occasional treat, not their routine diet. Cats, like people, seem to like some variety in their food although they clearly prefer some foods over others. They like several flavors of the Friskies Treats including this one. I buy a canister maybe every 2 months.
customer_reviews.author: Karl Weaver

customer_reviews.title: Affordable. Cats gobble them up and purr for more.
customer_reviews.text: My neighbor has two cats that enter my apartment's kitchen window using the fire escape. I normally buy temptations mix ups treats and they gobble them up no matter the flavor. I decided to purchase Friskies brand because it's 4 oz more, costs a little less, and I wanted to mix things up for them. They like these treats, but not as much as temptations treats. So I am going to put these in the rotation. The container had an inner seal and came fresh. I took away a star because once I got to the bottom of the container most of the treats were crumbs. Not good. I included (3) pictures in this review. That's all.
customer_reviews.author: grand-poobah

customer_reviews.title: The kitties come running!
customer_reviews.text: I regularly purchase Friskies Party Treat canisters on Amazon to treat the furballs! Ocean Whitefish is definitely their favorite flavor, and both always come running when they hear the canister being opened. I also use the washed empty canisters for craft containers, holding beads or other small items, which are easy to see thru the clear plastic. Love this kind of storage! Amazon has the most economical pricing and variety of flavors, and subscription delivery always ensures they don't go treatless! The kitties definitely have me trained to use these delightful treats! 💓🐾
customer_reviews.author: E. Dennis

customer_reviews.title: Senior kitty crack
customer_reviews.text: My 18 year old cat loves these treats. She would live on them if I let her. She is pretty picky, so if she likes something, she gets it. I wish they were made of better ingredients, but a little digestive powder on them (I add it to the canister and shake it around to coat the treats) and she is good to go. It’s a great value if you spend money to spoil your pets and the large size means you don’t need to buy as often and it’s a better overall value. They make my senior diva very happy, so I’m going to buy them. The fair price point just makes me happy.
customer_reviews.author: L. Jacobson

customer_reviews.title: Misty says "Go for it!"
customer_reviews.text: Misty is the one who should give the review as she is the cat that is spoiled by these treats...she likes most of the various flavors that are available. These do not make her ill. Some other brands we have tried makes her ill within minutes. Not sure just what the issue may be there. Overall Misty says these are fine and that she would like the other cats out there to know that she has enjoyed them for years now. Product as described, well packaged and shipped timely
customer_reviews.author: Dale H

customer_reviews.title: Pimpetts and Pimps loves these.
customer_reviews.text: I have 7 pimps and pimpetts ate the heck out of temptation treats. The temptations cost tooo much $14-16.00. I decided to try Friskies because of the cost. Table manners went out the door. I mean they eat and crack each piece so loud. Imagine 7 healthy robust pimps and pimpetts leaning into their bowls and crack, crack, crack, when done only crumbs left. Then they go into this hard running around the house, jumping over objects turning corners really hard. One hour of hardcore running then they finally, goes to sleep where they land. FRISKIES
customer_reviews.author: Jlo1st

customer_reviews.title: A treat my picky cats love!!!
customer_reviews.text: My cats are picky and I had just about given up on buying treats when this popped up as an add-on item when I was ordering cat food. I'm glad I did! My cats love love these little gems. I had to put them in a drawer as one of my cats loves them so much he attacked the container and actually made holes in the plastic trying to get some. I like that they are little bitty bites. They are perfect size for rewards. The container size is perfect for a three kitty household and the price is a good value. These have become a staple in the kitties pantry.
customer_reviews.author: Salem in Texas

customer_reviews.title: My cats love these
customer_reviews.text: My 3 girls love these treats, which are new for them. Even the one with no teeth! The treats smelled very fresh as soon as I opened the container. My cats know which packet or container holds which treats. When I show and shake a specific one, their reaction let's me know if that's the one they want. So far, this one is their new favorite by far! They go running to the spot they get their respective serving immediately! Fave before these was the Temptations brand, crunchy exterior and soft inside. I still give the hairball type of the Temptations (bought here, of course) but this Frisky version is now the first I offer.
customer_reviews.author: KadyOneTop Contributor: Cooking

customer_reviews.title: ... my life) and I've never seen them go nuts like this for a treat
customer_reviews.text: I've been giving treats since I've had cats (all my life) and I've never seen them go nuts like this for a treat. Not even for human food, even meat! It's a bit scary if you wanna know the truth! One, that is usually very patient, screams and paws at me if I take too long...the other, I am fearful may remove part of my finger if I'm not quick, ao I just throw her piece down and jerk my hand back. I am slightly concerned with the ingredients and how fattening they are. They really seem to have a lot of unnecessary crap in them, like everything these days.
customer_reviews.author: Rachel LeCureux

customer_reviews.title: Socks loves Friskies
customer_reviews.text: Socks adopted us. We started watering her in the summer, then next came snacks. Next came a bed for her. But now that it is getting really cold we got her a little heated house for outside, as she is still skittish with us, but warming up finally. Well, next came food for her, and enough for a midday snack too. Now she runs out to meet us when we come home, and walks us back to the patio. Tried cheaper cat food, but she wouldn’t eat it. So she is now a solely Friskies cat.
customer_reviews.author: Dovie

customer_reviews.title: Kitty crack
customer_reviews.text: I need to put these on subscription. This stuff must have kitty crack in it or something. I've had cats my whole life and I've never seen them beg for anything as much as these treats. They wake me up in the morning begging for it. They won't let me head up stairs after work until I'll given them their evening treat. I just wish I could find a crafty use for the empty containers.
customer_reviews.author: S. Freeman

customer_reviews.title: Cat Heaven
customer_reviews.text: Our old fat cat loves these. Except for the cap taking a lot to unscrew and open, the mix and flavors are certainly a cat favorite. Shake the jug and our cat comes running. And the size is perfect for at least a month for our one cat. We love the stay fresh container. The only thing missing is some catnip in the mix, but we purchased another Amazon cat treat that does have catnip as a part of the mix, combined the two in a bowl and then put them back in the containers. Our can have the best of both products now and loves them.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Made my cat throw up.
customer_reviews.text: I had been buying these for years! But I bought one pack of this in the big container, and ARGH! Puke every time I try to give them. BAH. Don't know if they changed the recipe or if I've just been getting garbage or old product, I still won't buy again.
customer_reviews.author: A. Brue

customer_reviews.title: the only dry treats my cat will each
customer_reviews.text: my 13 year old tabby is very picky. she only eats party mix for dry treats. every time i can find a 30 oz container of them i try and get it for her. she gets some every night . My dad gives her just a little bit at the very top of her kitty tree/condo and she expects it from him . if hes ever even a minute late she sits at the top of the condo and stares down at him. we have never seen this flavor in the stores.
customer_reviews.author: Tj

customer_reviews.title: Makes my cats happy.
customer_reviews.text: My cats love these treats and they are very picky eaters. If I want their attention, all I have to do is shake the container and they’re at my feet. Probably be a great training tool. What am I thinking? They train us. Anyone who doubts the intelligence of a cat has never interacted with one on a daily basis. My cats are brothers with completely different personalities. But, they do agree that these treats are yummy.
customer_reviews.author: butitsadryheat

customer_reviews.title: Friskies cat treats in 30 oz. canister is a great buy. My cats say buy more!
customer_reviews.text: Friskies cat treats in the 30 oz. canister is a super buy. My cats love these things and beg for them several times a day. I always fed mine on their cat tree so that’s where they run to and meow loudly while looking at me when I walk by. It’s so funny. Even my Jack Russell has gotten in on the act, begging with the cats. He thinks he is one of them, running to the stand. He gobbles them up too. They must be delicious!
customer_reviews.author: MCB catlady

customer_reviews.title: Django Says "MEOW!" Which Means "More NOW!"
customer_reviews.text: OMG, my cat loves these! I can hear him trying to open the cabinet to get them right now! These treats were far less expensive than I could find them locally, and they are obviously fresh, or my cats would not be nuts for them.

customer_reviews.title: My cats beg for these

Thanks for a great product

customer_reviews.author: Trixie P.

customer_reviews.title: Party Mix for my senior cat
customer_reviews.text: I got a small bag of the Friskies Party Treats just to give my kitties some variety with their treats. One of my senior cats tried them and now refuses her other treats. So when I found the tub of them I had to buy. They are hard and crunchy treats, my senior cat had no trounle with them. They are amout dime size maybe a little smaller.
customer_reviews.author: Danielleshu

customer_reviews.title: Treats for my spoiled furchild.
customer_reviews.text: This was a wonderful deal. I am guilty of spoiling my dear fur child, but it's nice to be able to find such a great deal that allows me to do so. The container seals securely. It has quite a lot of treats and these are some of my furchild, Mimzy's favorites. She knows the sound of the treat bin and with a container this size, I will get to see her come running as often as I like without fearing for the budget or supply.
customer_reviews.author: Christa Bertleson

customer_reviews.title: The cats line up at EXACTLY 11pm on our bed, all 4 of 'em for THESE Treats! Then they STARE at us!
customer_reviews.text: 4 cats can't be wrong!! They all love these treats and it's the highlight of their day. They show up at 11pm, exactly, and line up in the exact same order each night to get their treats doled out by "daddy" cat. How do they know it's 11pm?? Gosh, we'd have a riot if we didn't have these treats to feed them...it's fun for us too.
customer_reviews.author: Poopsie Efficient

customer_reviews.title: Great hard treat that keeps them coming back.
customer_reviews.text: My cat says these are alright. I got him a treat meal dispensing ball which I put these in to encourage him to figure it out with. These are worth it to him to push the ball around and get food. Both of our cats actually like them quite nicely and being a hard treat I'm quite pleased that they will eat them. They used to prefer only the soft ones -- but I guess they are growing up. The container is nice to store in the cupboard and the instantly know the sound as soon as you pick it up. Great option for treats -- varied size and shapes (cuz your cat totally cares).
customer_reviews.author: BluePandaTop Contributor: Activewear

customer_reviews.title: Best cat treat for a great price.
customer_reviews.text: My cat's go berserk for this cat treat. I used to buy a bottle that was 15 oz and cost about $9.00 a bottle at walmart. It was a better price when Sam's club sold 2 bottles for $15 but then Sams went out of business in Alaska. These treats are not only half the price, the bottle is 20 ounces and my cats come running from wherever they are (the dogs too) when I shake the bottle. I purchase 2 bottles a month (for my four cats and a couple of small dogs) for treats everyday and to get them to do what I want. LOL.
customer_reviews.author: Anna Cummings

customer_reviews.title: Meow.

The canister keeps the treats fresher than the bags, thank goodness. Like everything, the price has gone up, so keeping them fresh is important. Except for the price, I’m happy if he’s happy.

customer_reviews.title: Cat approved
customer_reviews.text: Well my cats absolutely love these! I mix them in their dry cat food ( not a lot) and they eat more and aren't so picky. They get some every night as an enticement to come in the bedroom as I have to keep them in there with me as we run a B and B and, if left in the other part of my loft, they would spend all night zooming around a running around like two bull elephants! Lol you all know what I mean! They love all flavor sand I "mix them up" for them. I love my Sammie and my misty and want to spoil them and these seem to do the trick. Great price too!
customer_reviews.author: Sjh

customer_reviews.title: Less expensive that other treats
customer_reviews.text: I have been giving y 7 cats Temptations for years and they love them. But it’s been costing me a fortune. Then I found Purina Party Mix, which was much less expensive and decided to try it. My kitties just love them! In fact one of the girls will only eat the Purina brand now. I still buy both but am slowly getting them all used to the Purina. Hope they’ll all decide to switch so I can save some $$$!
customer_reviews.author: JoyDesigns

customer_reviews.title: 🐈❤🐈❤🐈❤🐈❤

customer_reviews.author: Non stop shopper

customer_reviews.title: Control the food- control the cat !
customer_reviews.text: I go through these huge containers like water. Well, when you have 6-8 cats......you go there ! Always fresh, nice and crunchy (providing your cat actually chews his food) stand up well to being tossed down the hall way or flinging across the room for search and find missions! Cats cant get enough of these. Mine ALL love them, unlike some treats I have brought home and then gotten the stare of death upon rejection! Even my dogs like them, not that I like that, but they do- Been buying these for years, will continue!
customer_reviews.author: lance bingham

customer_reviews.title: Not for cats with sensitive stomachs
customer_reviews.text: Although this was a good brand that has been around forever and I have given it to past cats and it has been fine...my cat I have currently had a sensitive stomach when it came to these treats. He didn’t have a lot, but he vomited four times since I started giving it to him. It may not be the treats but for cats with sensitive stomachs I definitely would just look into grain free snacks.
customer_reviews.author: Lexie

customer_reviews.title: Great price, fast shipping.
customer_reviews.text: Luckily these apparently delicious cat treats come in a plastic container... they will do anything to get to the crunchy nibbles inside. We've put these up in a hutch where the only way to get into it is by lifting the handle upward and allowing the latch to catch.... we've put them in drawers, cabinets, closets, and a few times we've had to put them in the safe. Our three cats will tear apart everything to get to their treats. Also, this happens to be cheaper than the store we were purchasing them at.
customer_reviews.author: Baka Baka

customer_reviews.title: Kahuna Crunch is a hit!
customer_reviews.text: Sure, I read the appalling ingredients, but I only give 5 pieces at a time to each cat and it makes them happy. I would not fit into this mix, however, if they could open the lids! I have tried all 3-4 flavours, can't really they like one better then the other, all great to them.

customer_reviews.author: Janet L

customer_reviews.title: Competitive pricing, well liked by my cats
customer_reviews.text: All my cats but one love this flavor and snack type. The odd one likes the chicken version of Party Mix. Treats should be bigger, perhaps dog kibble size, to clean teeth. I do use Greenies, too, and all three cats still eat them whole.

Next time, I'll read the label more carefully and get the Meow Mix, or something more mellow than a Party Mix.
